   "source": [
    "## Section 1: Introduction to Bond Features & Cash Flows\n",
    "\n",
    "A bond is essentially a loan made by an investor to a borrower (typically corporate or governmental). The borrower promises to pay back the loan amount at a specified future date and, in most cases, to make periodic interest payments to the investor.\n",
    "\n",
    "Key features of a typical fixed-coupon bond include:\n",
    "\n",
    "*   **Par Value (Face Value or Principal):** The amount of money that the bond issuer promises to repay at maturity. This is usually $1,000 or $100.\n",
    "*   **Coupon Rate:** The annual interest rate that the bond issuer promises to pay, expressed as a percentage of the par value. \n",
    "*   **Coupon Payment:** The actual amount of interest paid periodically (e.g., semi-annually or annually). Calculated as `(Coupon Rate * Par Value) / Number of Coupon Payments per Year`.\n",
    "*   **Maturity Date:** The date on which the bond issuer must repay the par value to the bondholder.\n",
    "*   **Coupon Frequency:** The number of times per year the coupon is paid (e.g., 1 for annual, 2 for semi-annual)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Visualizing a Bond's Cash Flows\n",
    "\n",
    "A bond's life can be visualized as a timeline of cash flows. For a typical fixed-coupon bond:\n",
    "\n",
    "*   At time 0 (issuance or purchase), there might be an outflow if you buy the bond (its price).\n",
    "*   At regular intervals (e.g., every 6 months or 1 year), the bondholder receives a fixed coupon payment.\n",
    "*   At the maturity date, the bondholder receives the final coupon payment plus the par value of the bond.\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's set up some interactive widgets to define a bond's parameters and then display its cash flow schedule."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": [],
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Interactive Widgets for Bond Parameters\n",
    "par_value_widget = FloatSlider(value=1000, min=100, max=10000, step=100, description='Par Value ($):', readout_format='$,.0f')\n",
    "coupon_rate_widget = FloatSlider(value=5, min=0, max=20, step=0.1, description='Coupon Rate (%):', readout_format='.1f')\n",
    "years_to_maturity_widget = IntSlider(value=5, min=1, max=30, step=1, description='Maturity (Yrs):')\n",
    "coupon_frequency_widget = widgets.Dropdown(options=[('Annual', 1), ('Semi-Annual', 2)], value=2, description='Coupon Freq:')\n",
    "\n",
    "ui = VBox([\n",
    "    par_value_widget, \n",
    "    coupon_rate_widget, \n",
    "    years_to_maturity_widget, \n",
    "    coupon_frequency_widget\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "def display_cash_flows(par_value, annual_coupon_rate, years_to_maturity, coupon_frequency):\n",
    "    num_coupons = years_to_maturity * coupon_frequency\n",
    "    coupon_payment = (annual_coupon_rate / 100 * par_value) / coupon_frequency\n",
