    "## Section 2: Bond Pricing\n",
    "\n",
    "The price of a bond is the present value of all its expected future cash flows (coupon payments and par value repayment) discounted at an appropriate market discount rate (also known as yield or yield-to-maturity for this context).\n",
    "\n",
    "The formula for a fixed-coupon bond is:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ P = \\sum_{t=1}^{N} \\frac{C_t}{(1+y)^t} + \\frac{FV}{(1+y)^N} $$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where:\n",
    "*   `P` = Price of the bond\n",
    "*   `C_t` = Coupon payment at time `t`\n",
    "*   `FV` = Face Value (Par Value) of the bond\n",
    "*   `y` = Discount rate per period (Market Yield / Coupon Frequency)\n",
    "*   `N` = Total number of periods (Years to Maturity * Coupon Frequency)\n",
    "\n",
    "Let's create a function to calculate this."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": [],
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_bond_price(par_value, annual_coupon_rate, years_to_maturity, annual_market_yield, coupon_frequency=2):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculates the price of a fixed-coupon bond.\"\"\"\n",
    "    if years_to_maturity <= 0:\n",
    "        return par_value # Or handle as an error/matured bond\n",
    "    \n",
    "    num_periods = years_to_maturity * coupon_frequency\n",
    "    coupon_payment_per_period = (annual_coupon_rate / 100 * par_value) / coupon_frequency\n",
    "    discount_rate_per_period = (annual_market_yield / 100) / coupon_frequency\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Calculate PV of coupon payments (an annuity)\n",
    "    pv_coupons = 0\n",
    "    if discount_rate_per_period > 0:\n",
    "        pv_coupons = coupon_payment_per_period * (1 - (1 + discount_rate_per_period)**-num_periods) / discount_rate_per_period\n",
    "    else: # If discount rate is zero, PV is just sum of undiscounted coupons\n",
    "        pv_coupons = coupon_payment_per_period * num_periods\n",
    "        \n",
    "    # Calculate PV of par value\n",
    "    pv_par_value = par_value / (1 + discount_rate_per_period)**num_periods\n",
    "    \n",
    "    bond_price = pv_coupons + pv_par_value\n",
    "    return bond_price\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example Usage:\n",
    "example_price = calculate_bond_price(par_value=1000, annual_coupon_rate=5, years_to_maturity=5, annual_market_yield=4, coupon_frequency=2)\n",
    "print(f\"Example Bond Price (5yr, 5% coupon, 4% yield, semi-annual): ${example_price:,.2f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "example_price_at_par = calculate_bond_price(par_value=1000, annual_coupon_rate=5, years_to_maturity=5, annual_market_yield=5, coupon_frequency=2)\n",
    "print(f\"Example Bond Price (5yr, 5% coupon, 5% yield, semi-annual): ${example_price_at_par:,.2f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "example_price_discount = calculate_bond_price(par_value=1000, annual_coupon_rate=5, years_to_maturity=5, annual_market_yield=6, coupon_frequency=2)\n",
    "print(f\"Example Bond Price (5yr, 5% coupon, 6% yield, semi-annual): ${example_price_discount:,.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
