    "### Current Yield\n",
    "\n",
    "Current Yield is a simpler measure that relates the annual coupon payment to the bond's current market price.\n",
    "\n",
    "$$ \\text{Current Yield} = \\frac{\\text{Annual Coupon Payment}}{\\text{Current Market Price}} $$\n",
    "\n",
    "**Limitations of Current Yield:**\n",
    "*   It only considers the coupon interest and ignores the capital gain or loss if the bond is held to maturity (i.e., the difference between par value and purchase price).\n",
    "*   It doesn't account for the time value of money for all cash flows.\n",
    "\n",
    "However, it provides a quick snapshot of the return generated by the coupon payments relative to the current price."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": [],
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calculate_current_yield(current_price, par_value, annual_coupon_rate):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculates the Current Yield of a bond.\"\"\"\n",
    "    if current_price <= 0:\n",
    "        return float('nan') # Avoid division by zero\n",
    "    annual_coupon_payment = (annual_coupon_rate / 100) * par_value\n",
    "    current_yield = (annual_coupon_payment / current_price) * 100 # As a percentage\n",
    "    return current_yield\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example Usage:\n",
    "cy_example1 = calculate_current_yield(current_price=1043.76, par_value=1000, annual_coupon_rate=5)\n",
    "print(f\"Example Current Yield for a bond priced at $1043.76: {cy_example1:.4f}%\")\n",
    "\n",
    "cy_example2 = calculate_current_yield(current_price=958.42, par_value=1000, annual_coupon_rate=5)\n",
    "print(f\"Example Current Yield for a bond priced at $958.42: {cy_example2:.4f}%\")"
